1
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:02,878
(gasps)

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:04,588
(water bubbling)

3
00:00:12,179 --> 00:00:14,014
YESOOL: When did I start

4
00:00:14,765 --> 00:00:17,184
having this dream?

5
00:00:18,769 --> 00:00:21,104
Is this a dream too?

6
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:27,527
It must be.

7
00:00:29,154 --> 00:00:30,697
Then...

8
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:34,076
it's time for me to wake up now.

9
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:37,996
I don't know what happens after this.

10
00:00:42,834 --> 00:00:45,045
(suspenseful music)

11
00:00:51,802 --> 00:00:53,345
(bubbling)

12
00:00:56,223 --> 00:00:57,432
(Minhu blows)

13
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:06,984
HAEJIN: It's all because of you!

14
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:10,612
You're the one who put Yesool in danger!

15
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,616
I told you to get away from Yesool!

16
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,868
-(Haejin grunts)
-(Minhu groans)

17
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:18,245
(Haejin grunts)

18
00:01:19,955 --> 00:01:21,832
(grunting)

19
00:01:23,125 --> 00:01:24,960
(fainted grunt)

20
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:28,255
(breathes deeply)

21
00:01:33,385 --> 00:01:34,636
(softly)
Mr. Cha.

22
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:39,683
(suspenseful music stops)

23
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:45,647
Mr. Cha.

24
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,444
(grunting)

25
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,781
No.
(breathes deeply)

26
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:57,451
Mr. Cha, wake up.

27
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:00,829
No.
(sobbing)

28
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:02,664
Come on, open your eyes.

29
00:02:02,748 --> 00:02:03,832
Mr. Cha.

30
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:05,375
Mr. Cha.

31
00:02:06,168 --> 00:02:07,544
Mr. Cha!

32
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,379
Mr. Cha!
(sobbing continues)

33
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:12,966
(Yesool sobbing)

34
00:02:16,887 --> 00:02:18,805
(gasps)

35
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:21,600
(siren blaring)

36
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:25,062
EPISODE 12

37
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:32,110
(tires screech)

38
00:02:32,194 --> 00:02:33,320
Kim Haejin!

39
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:34,655
Who are you?

40
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:36,365
-Let go of me!
-Grab him!

41
00:02:36,448 --> 00:02:38,659
Let go!
(screaming)

42
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:43,580
You are under arrest for
the murder of Mr. Hong in the year 2000.

43
00:02:43,664 --> 00:02:47,084
You have the right to consult an attorney,
and you have the right to remain silent.

44
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,669
You may refuse to answer any questions.

45
00:02:48,752 --> 00:02:50,629
-Take him.
-Yes, sir.

46
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:53,632
(somber music)

47
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:58,553
(grunting)

48
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:02,057
I didn't kill him.

49
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,975
I didn't kill him. I'm Yesool's father.

50
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:05,310
I didn't kill him.

51
00:03:05,394 --> 00:03:07,396
I'm Yesool's father. I'm her father.

52
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,772
(sobbing)

53
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,190
OFFICER: Here! Over here!

54
00:03:11,108 --> 00:03:13,318
(Yesool sobbing)

55
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:17,197
(Yesool breathes deeply)

56
00:03:26,665 --> 00:03:27,666
(siren blaring)

57
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,543
-How are his vitals?
-OFFICER: They're dropping.

58
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:31,920
There's a deep 5-cm stab wound,
and the bleeding is bad.

59
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:34,005
(Yesool sobbing)

60
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:37,259
You can't go in here.

61
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,599
AMBULANCES ONLY

62
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:50,105
(sobbing)
No.

63
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:54,025
Yesool.

64
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,862
Mom.

65
00:03:56,945 --> 00:03:58,947
(sobbing continues)

66
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:01,450
(music stops)

67
00:04:10,292 --> 00:04:11,334
Yesool.

68
00:04:12,419 --> 00:04:14,463
I'm sure that Minhu will be fine.

69
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:19,801
You knew everything, didn't you?

70
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:26,558
Mr. Cha and I...

71
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:30,979
have known each other
since we were young, right?

72
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:33,106
(light music)

73
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:38,612
(young Yesool sobbing)

74
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:42,657
WELCOME NOEL ORPHANAGE

75
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:46,286
(sobbing continues)

76
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,213
Who are you?

77
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,381
Are you new here?

78
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:01,635
Where are you from?

79
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:03,929
Seoul.

80
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,265
Why aren't you going inside?

81
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:13,146
Did your mom tell you
to wait here for a minute?

82
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,440
That she'll come back for you?

83
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,612
Well, she lied.

84
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:27,869
Want to know
what's going to happen to you?

85
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:31,414
No matter how long you wait,

86
00:05:32,082 --> 00:05:33,166
she's not coming back.

87
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,418
(sobbing)

88
00:05:37,254 --> 00:05:38,880
If you cry like that,

89
00:05:39,548 --> 00:05:42,509
you'll only make it
hard and painful for yourself.

90
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:44,594
It'll be your loss.

91
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,805
Don't waste your energy.

92
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:53,395
(sobbing)
I'm lost.

93
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:57,858
I moved here today.

94
00:06:05,407 --> 00:06:06,533
You moved here?

95
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:09,452
It's a two-story red-brick house.

96
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:13,206
But I don't know where it is.

97
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:16,793
(sobbing continues)

98
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:19,629
Follow me.

99
00:06:23,675 --> 00:06:24,885
Come on.

100
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:35,312
(light music)

101
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:45,280
(dog barking in distance)

102
00:06:47,157 --> 00:06:49,326
Is this it? This is your house?

103
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,911
No, it's not.

104
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,750
Okay. Let's try another house, then.

105
00:06:59,586 --> 00:07:01,588
(light music)

106
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,888
YOUNG MINHU: I think this might be it.

107
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:13,558
It looks similar,
but it's not the right one.

108
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:16,102
Really?

109
00:07:16,186 --> 00:07:18,647
SMILE GROCERY STORE

110
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:23,610
Excuse me.

111
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:27,447
She just moved into
a two-story red-brick house.

112
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,616
Do you know where it is?

113
00:07:30,075 --> 00:07:32,243
I'm not sure.

114
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,579
Thank you.

115
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:37,832
(sighs)

116
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:43,963
(tire screech)

117
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:51,304
(foreboding music)

118
00:08:00,230 --> 00:08:01,439
(sighs)

119
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:06,861
(exhales deeply)

120
00:08:18,373 --> 00:08:19,374
Mom!

121
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:20,917
Yesool!

122
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:21,918
Yesool!

123
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:24,003
(Sara gasping)

124
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:28,550
(Sara sobbing)
I'm so sorry.

125
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:33,847
-Are you hurt?
-No.

126
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:39,269
YOUNG YESOOL:
I was scared, but that boy helped me.

127
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,771
Hey, wait a minute.

128
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:47,485
I'm Yesool's father.

129
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:49,112
What's your name?

130
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:51,406
Minhu.

131
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:52,866
Okay, Minhu.

132
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:54,451
Thanks.

133
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:56,703
Where do you live?

134
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:59,289
I want to thank your parents
or something...

135
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,334
I don't have any.

136
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:07,005
I don't have any.

137
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:08,256
Parents, I mean.

138
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:12,761
I live...

139
00:09:14,054 --> 00:09:15,221
at an orphanage.

140
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:18,475
Okay. I'm sorry.

141
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,352
Then I can just thank you, right?

142
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:27,901
Thank you so much
for taking care of Yesool.

143
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:29,486
Thanks.

144
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:33,323
We'll be sure
to pay you a visit next time.

145
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:34,407
Okay.

146
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:36,826
Goodbye.

147
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:44,501
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

148
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,463
-Are you hungry?
-Yes.

149
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:54,344
SUNGJOON: Look at your mom.
(chuckles)

150
00:09:55,929 --> 00:10:00,350
"Little Red Riding Hood and the granny
burst out of the wolf's belly.

151
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:04,437
Little Red Riding Hood,
who was saved by the hunter,

152
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:08,650
lived with the granny happily ever after."

153
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:09,692
LITTLE RED RIDING HOOD

154
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:15,573
I'm sorry, Yesool.

155
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:20,245
Mommy and Daddy are both sorry
for leaving you alone.

156
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:29,963
But you made a friend
as soon as you moved here.

157
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:32,090
He's not my friend.

158
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:33,258
He's not?

159
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:36,678
You read to me when I can't sleep,

160
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,639
and you're with me all the time.

161
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:41,432
But a friend can't do that.

162
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:46,229
So, I'm going to become
his family instead.

163
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:48,398
Do you like him that much?

164
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,024
Yes. I do.

165
00:10:51,234 --> 00:10:53,611
I like you more, though.

166
00:10:54,529 --> 00:10:55,530
Dad.

167
00:10:55,905 --> 00:10:59,159
Let's live happily ever after,
just like in the storybooks.

168
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:01,619
Of course.

169
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:10,795
Where's my stuff? Where is it?

170
00:11:10,879 --> 00:11:12,297
It's not here!

171
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,174
You stole it, didn't you?

172
00:11:14,257 --> 00:11:15,842
You did. Tell me.

173
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:17,677
Spill it!

174
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,554
YOUNG YESOOL:
Don't you dare mess with him!

175
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:26,352
(panting)

176
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:36,946
(light music)

177
00:11:44,996 --> 00:11:47,332
(Young Yesool yells)

178
00:11:49,751 --> 00:11:51,002
Let's just go.

179
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:56,758
(quirky music)

180
00:12:01,763 --> 00:12:03,097
Are you a baby?

181
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:05,433
Whatever.

182
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,644
You're younger than me.

183
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:20,406
(light music)

184
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:26,788
You think you can just clench your fists

185
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:28,748
and hold back your tears,

186
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:30,708
and everything will be fine?

187
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:38,549
If you want to cry, you should cry.
That means you're strong.

188
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:40,468
That's what Dad said.

189
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,347
If you're happy, laugh.
If you're annoyed, complain.

190
00:12:45,765 --> 00:12:49,185
He said that's what strong people do.

191
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:58,653
I can take care of those kids for you.

192
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:05,493
So play with me.

193
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,288
(light music)

194
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:26,723
Is it not there?

195
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,685
No. Let me look just a bit more.

196
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,397
(water sloshing)

197
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,274
(both laugh)

198
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:39,277
That's cold!

199
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:41,154
YOUNG YESOOL: Stop it!

200
00:13:41,863 --> 00:13:43,489
YOUNG MINHU: Stop it, you.

201
00:13:43,573 --> 00:13:45,575
(both laugh)

202
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:48,494
"He wanted to go on an adventure.

203
00:13:48,578 --> 00:13:51,873
He wanted to catch bigger
and tastier fish.

204
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:55,877
Kimi made up his mind,
and ran to ask his parents.

205
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:59,589
'Mom, Dad, may I go to
the seaside village tomorrow?'

206
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,299
'Sure.'"

207
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:04,427
(light music)

208
00:14:16,022 --> 00:14:18,399
(birds chirping)

209
00:14:20,443 --> 00:14:21,986
Minhu, your painting is...

210
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:25,073
It's very dreamlike.

211
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:28,743
Why don't you use
your favorite color right here?

212
00:14:29,494 --> 00:14:31,537
-How about yellow?
-Sure.

213
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:33,372
I'll help, Minhu.

214
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:34,582
Let's do it together.

215
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:38,377
(playful music)

216
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:53,309
YOUNG YESOOL: Look.

217
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:55,436
What color did you use?

218
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,396
YOUNG YESOOL: Green and pink.

219
00:14:57,688 --> 00:14:59,232
YOUNG MINHU: Green and pink?

220
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:00,525
That's so pretty.

221
00:15:00,608 --> 00:15:01,734
YOUNG YESOOL: Right?

222
00:15:02,110 --> 00:15:03,820
REPORTER:
We're predicting heavy rain tomorrow.

223
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:06,656
We're also expecting to see
the first super blood moon in 22 years,

224
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:09,826
which is a combination
of a total lunar eclipse and super moon.

225
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:14,247
The Native Americans used to believe that
a super blood moon would grant you a wish.

226
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:16,833
Let's hope it appears
through the heavy rainfall.

227
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:19,544
We also hope to become
such a miracle for you as well.

228
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:22,505
That's all we have for you today.
Thank you for watching.

229
00:15:26,676 --> 00:15:27,969
It's Dad's ad.

230
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:30,805
Oh, is that me?

231
00:15:33,224 --> 00:15:34,267
You're awesome, Dad!

232
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:40,523
How do you make an advertisement?

233
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:43,776
Hmm.

234
00:15:44,819 --> 00:15:45,987
You just need to...

235
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,072
love people.

236
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:50,783
What does that mean?

237
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:53,744
Making an advertisement

238
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:58,749
is sharing what you have with others.

239
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:05,631
So, if you have jealousy in your heart,
you'll just end up sharing jealousy.

240
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:08,259
If you have hate, then you'll share hate.

241
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:12,597
But if you have kindness,

242
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:15,183
then you can share
that kindness with others.

243
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:17,226
If you have love,

244
00:16:17,727 --> 00:16:19,437
you can share love too.

245
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:21,022
For me,

246
00:16:21,606 --> 00:16:23,399
that's what advertisements are.

247
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:31,199
YOUNG MINHU: It's raining so much
all of a sudden.

248
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:36,329
Let's go inside.

249
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:37,538
YOUNG YESOOL: It's cold.

250
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:41,209
(young Minhu breathes deeply)
You had fun today, right?

251
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:43,085
YOUNG YESOOL:
Yes. Let's do it again tomorrow.

252
00:16:44,754 --> 00:16:46,214
What's wrong?

253
00:16:46,672 --> 00:16:48,216
Aren't you going inside?

254
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,051
Hmm?

255
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:55,264
Is somebody there?

256
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:58,309
(tense music)

257
00:17:02,647 --> 00:17:03,731
YOUNG MINHU: Be quiet.

258
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:06,484
Why?

259
00:17:09,445 --> 00:17:10,613
Yesool.

260
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:13,824
Close your eyes really tight

261
00:17:14,784 --> 00:17:16,077
and just count to ten.

262
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:18,746
I'll be right back.

263
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:20,665
-(thunder rumbles)
-Okay.

264
00:17:28,089 --> 00:17:31,384
-YOUNG YESOOL: One. Two.
-(young Minhu panting)

265
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:41,477
Seven.

266
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:44,605
(thunder rumbling)

267
00:17:48,943 --> 00:17:49,944
YOUNG YESOOL: Minhu.

268
00:17:51,112 --> 00:17:53,406
(gasps)
Yesool!

269
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,658
(ominous music)

270
00:17:55,741 --> 00:17:57,118
-YOUNG MINHU: Come on, quick.
-YOUNG YESOOL: Why?

271
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:58,619
Quickly!

272
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:01,372
(ominous music continues)

273
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,793
-Careful.
-Okay.

274
00:18:09,005 --> 00:18:11,215
