I knew that this would happen.

369
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:24,893
(somber music)

370
00:27:28,605 --> 00:27:30,190
I didn't know that I did,

371
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:34,194
but I think I knew.

372
00:27:34,278 --> 00:27:37,281
(sobbing)

373
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:44,705
Don't cry, Yesool.

374
00:27:46,081 --> 00:27:47,124
It's okay.

375
00:27:47,499 --> 00:27:48,917
It's all going to be okay.

376
00:27:48,959 --> 00:27:51,169
SARA: I didn't know
what you meant at first.

377
00:27:51,253 --> 00:27:52,379
Don't cry.

378
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:53,964
Later,

379
00:27:54,715 --> 00:27:57,092
I figured you might have
gained that ability

380
00:27:57,175 --> 00:27:58,844
because of what happened back then.

381
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:02,389
After that,

382
00:28:03,432 --> 00:28:05,642
I couldn't bear
to stay in Korea any longer,

383
00:28:06,268 --> 00:28:08,061
so I went to the United States.

384
00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:11,982
You still should have told me.

385
00:28:13,567 --> 00:28:15,903
I didn't know about any of this.

386
00:28:21,158 --> 00:28:22,826
(sobbing)

387
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:24,077
I'm sorry.

388
00:28:26,997 --> 00:28:30,000
But I did it for you.

389
00:28:31,877 --> 00:28:33,921
I thought it was all over.

390
00:28:35,589 --> 00:28:37,424
I didn't think he would do this.

391
00:28:40,844 --> 00:28:42,679
NURSE: Is Cha Minhu's guardian here?

392
00:28:47,935 --> 00:28:51,438
We stopped the internal bleeding,
but he had already lost a lot of blood.

393
00:28:51,939 --> 00:28:54,483
There seems to have been an issue
with the blood flow to the brain.

394
00:28:55,359 --> 00:28:57,402
Because of that,
his vitals are still unstable.

395
00:28:58,236 --> 00:29:00,155
He might regain consciousness,

396
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:03,075
but you may need to prepare yourself.

397
00:29:05,535 --> 00:29:06,828
Yesool.

398
00:29:09,122 --> 00:29:11,333
(somber music)

399
00:29:14,628 --> 00:29:16,838
(sobbing)

400
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:28,183
Minhu, I'll be right back.

401
00:29:29,226 --> 00:29:31,353
I promise that I'll find you.

402
00:29:31,436 --> 00:29:34,106
So wait for me until then.

403
00:29:34,815 --> 00:29:35,857
Okay?

404
00:29:41,738 --> 00:29:44,408
Did it ever occur to you that maybe
you're the one who can't remember

405
00:29:44,491 --> 00:29:45,492
pretty much everything?

406
00:29:48,328 --> 00:29:49,496
Bye.

407
00:29:52,124 --> 00:29:55,711
I bet Mr. Cha was so mad at me.

408
00:29:56,628 --> 00:30:00,716
How could I have forgotten everything?

409
00:30:02,092 --> 00:30:03,677
Who painted that?

410
00:30:04,219 --> 00:30:05,971
Did you paint it yourself?

411
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:07,139
Oh, that?

412
00:30:07,764 --> 00:30:09,516
I was interrupted in the middle of it.

413
00:30:10,267 --> 00:30:11,226
By whom?

414
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:12,978
My first love.

415
00:30:15,939 --> 00:30:18,442
You even gave me so many hints.

416
00:30:24,197 --> 00:30:25,699
I still...

417
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:29,286
have so many things to say to you.

418
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:32,247
Come on. Wake up.

419
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:36,960
Say something like, "Did you just
figure it out, you stupid idiot?"

420
00:30:37,044 --> 00:30:38,211
(sniffles)

421
00:30:38,837 --> 00:30:41,381
You can sound super arrogant if you want.
(sobbing)

422
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:43,675
Come on.

423
00:30:44,801 --> 00:30:47,012
(somber music)

424
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:53,685
EUNCHONG UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

425
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:56,188
EOMJI: Oh.

426
00:30:58,648 --> 00:31:01,318
Damn it, where's Minhee?

427
00:31:01,401 --> 00:31:04,988
How come I still haven't gotten a response
for the Mopix advertisement draft?

428
00:31:05,072 --> 00:31:06,323
You sent it already?

429
00:31:06,406 --> 00:31:07,991
How many edits have we made so far?

430
00:31:08,075 --> 00:31:09,868
Three? Four?

431
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:11,745
(sobbing)

432
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:13,371
I don't know.

433
00:31:13,455 --> 00:31:16,208
They want us to make the logo smaller,
then make it bigger again,

434
00:31:16,291 --> 00:31:17,793
then change the background to a sunset.

435
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:19,127
(fake sobbing)

436
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:20,879
I gave up counting at that point.

437
00:31:20,962 --> 00:31:23,340
This one is the sixth edit.
I've been keeping count.

438
00:31:24,382 --> 00:31:27,594
But this is supposed to be the last one,
so I'll go and tell Mr. Cha...

439
00:31:31,681 --> 00:31:33,308
(all sigh)

440
00:31:33,391 --> 00:31:34,643
Wait.

441
00:31:35,143 --> 00:31:37,062
Hong Yesool's here today, right?

442
00:31:37,145 --> 00:31:38,313
Where is she?

443
00:31:38,396 --> 00:31:39,606
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

444
00:31:39,689 --> 00:31:41,024
Get out.

445
00:31:41,108 --> 00:31:42,859
I'm busy.

446
00:31:42,943 --> 00:31:44,820
Please make sure it's processed.

447
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:51,785
So, you're going to quit your job
so you can take care of Cha Minhu?

448
00:31:52,494 --> 00:31:55,455
If you quit, then who's going to
wrap up our Mopix project?

449
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:58,667
Isn't Planning Team 1 in charge of
the new Keple phone too?

450
00:32:00,377 --> 00:32:02,003
(sighs deeply)

451
00:32:04,589 --> 00:32:05,841
One month.

452
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:08,468
I'll cover your projects for one month.
Take a break and come back.

453
00:32:08,552 --> 00:32:09,803
No, ma'am.

454
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,764
I would like to resign.

455
00:32:12,848 --> 00:32:14,099
Why?

456
00:32:14,182 --> 00:32:16,268
You don't think Minhu's going to
wake up in a month?

457
00:32:16,852 --> 00:32:17,853
Ms. Jo.

458
00:32:17,936 --> 00:32:20,730
You know how hard Cha Minhu
worked on Keple, right?

459
00:32:21,231 --> 00:32:23,733
He's been waiting to bid on it
for so long.

460
00:32:23,817 --> 00:32:26,194
Do you really think
he'll miss that opportunity?

461
00:32:27,070 --> 00:32:30,699
Mr. Cha will wake up in a month for sure.

462
00:32:32,117 --> 00:32:34,578
So, go take a break for a month.

463
00:32:35,245 --> 00:32:37,122
I'll put it down as a leave of absence.

464
00:32:47,174 --> 00:32:48,550
You're not getting paid, though.

465
00:32:52,512 --> 00:32:54,431
(sighs deeply)

466
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,187
JIYOUNG: Minhu.

467
00:33:03,607 --> 00:33:06,693
Don't do this.
(sobbing)

468
00:33:09,571 --> 00:33:10,947
Minhu.

469
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:13,241
Why aren't you waking up?

470
00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:14,993
Geez, stop it.

471
00:33:15,076 --> 00:33:17,370
He'll get up soon, so stop crying.

472
00:33:17,454 --> 00:33:20,207
When? It's been two weeks already!

473
00:33:20,290 --> 00:33:22,959
So when exactly is he waking up?

474
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:26,087
Why aren't you saying anything?
Aren't you two supposed to be doctors?

475
00:33:26,171 --> 00:33:28,173
(Jiyoung sobs)

476
00:33:28,256 --> 00:33:31,635
Yes, you're right. I'm a crappy doctor.

477
00:33:31,718 --> 00:33:33,803
I should have gone
to general surgery instead.

478
00:33:33,887 --> 00:33:36,473
Both of you, be quiet.
You're probably bothering Minhu.

479
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:40,143
Minhu.

480
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:44,522
-Aren't you supposed to be somewhere else?
-That's not important right now!

481
00:33:44,606 --> 00:33:46,650
Minhu.

482
00:33:46,733 --> 00:33:48,818
(Jiyoung sobbing)

483
00:33:48,902 --> 00:33:50,570
Where's your manager?

484
00:33:50,654 --> 00:33:51,780
Get up.

485
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:53,156
Let's go, come on.

486
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:54,741
Come on, let's go! Get up, quick.

487
00:33:54,824 --> 00:33:56,743
Hey, get up. Come on. Let's go.

488
00:33:59,579 --> 00:34:02,624
-JIYOUNG: What's going to happen to Minhu?
-I said, he'll wake up soon.

489
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:05,669
-Hey. Breathe.
-(Jiyoung sobbing)

490
00:34:05,752 --> 00:34:07,545
Come on. We're leaving.

491
00:34:07,629 --> 00:34:10,674
This isn't what it looks like. We're fine.

492
00:34:10,757 --> 00:34:12,592
Come on.

493
00:34:14,344 --> 00:34:16,721
Is Doctor Oh going to skip his meal again?

494
00:34:16,805 --> 00:34:17,931
Yes.

495
00:34:18,014 --> 00:34:19,766
He's not been eating for days.

496
00:34:19,849 --> 00:34:22,352
I'm scared that he'll pass out
or something.

497
00:34:22,435 --> 00:34:23,687
No kidding.

498
00:34:23,770 --> 00:34:25,981
He never skipped meals before.

499
00:34:26,940 --> 00:34:29,693
Should we give him a glucose injection
while he's sleeping?

500
00:34:29,776 --> 00:34:31,569
If he actually passes out,

501
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:33,655
wouldn't that mean more work for us?

502
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:35,532
How can you say something like that?

503
00:34:35,615 --> 00:34:36,908
Just eat your food.

504
00:34:36,992 --> 00:34:39,411
(sighs deeply)

505
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:44,958
(somber music)

506
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:56,052
(knocking)

507
00:35:04,686 --> 00:35:07,188
-What are you doing?
-Huh?

508
00:35:07,272 --> 00:35:09,566
Didn't you see my text?
I was waiting for 20 minutes.

509
00:35:09,649 --> 00:35:10,775
A PK like me has to eat,

510
00:35:10,859 --> 00:35:13,278
go to the bathroom,
and brush our teeth in 20 minutes.

511
00:35:13,903 --> 00:35:16,114
You said you'd always come running
if I needed you.

512
00:35:17,073 --> 00:35:19,200
From now on, I won't wait
for more than five minutes.

513
00:35:23,455 --> 00:35:27,042
And I don't like men who are too skinny.

514
00:35:27,626 --> 00:35:30,462
So don't lose any more weight.
You're making me worry.

515
00:35:30,545 --> 00:35:32,756
(playful music)

516
00:35:37,469 --> 00:35:38,470
Howoo.

517
00:35:52,942 --> 00:35:54,944
(light music)

518
00:35:58,657 --> 00:36:02,160
I've always wanted to meet with you.

519
00:36:02,744 --> 00:36:07,415
I've heard so much about you from Minhu,
so you already seem pretty familiar.

520
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:10,877
I've heard a lot about you too, sir.

521
00:36:12,462 --> 00:36:15,548
Minhu has been worried
about you for a long time.

522
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:18,927
He's always thinking about

523
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:22,347
how to make you feel more comfortable.

524
00:36:25,975 --> 00:36:28,728
Ms. Hong. I may be a doctor,

525
00:36:28,812 --> 00:36:32,482
but I think that are
some things in this world

526
00:36:32,982 --> 00:36:34,275
that medicine can't explain.

527
00:36:35,652 --> 00:36:36,903
What do you...

528
00:36:37,821 --> 00:36:40,990
Maybe, the reason that the two of you
got your abilities is because

529
00:36:41,074 --> 00:36:43,451
you were trying to protect each other.

530
00:36:44,119 --> 00:36:45,787
At least, that's what I think.

531
00:36:46,913 --> 00:36:48,081
He's going to

532
00:36:48,665 --> 00:36:50,250
wake up soon.

533
00:36:50,875 --> 00:36:52,419
He's done his duty,

534
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:54,587
so he'll wake up soon,

535
00:36:56,172 --> 00:36:57,257
like nothing happened.

536
00:36:58,341 --> 00:37:00,385
I hope so too.

537
00:37:02,804 --> 00:37:05,014
(dramatic music)

538
00:37:11,604 --> 00:37:14,274
(cell phone vibrates)

539
00:37:16,693 --> 00:37:17,736
Yes?

540
00:37:17,819 --> 00:37:20,155
Are you Mr. Cha Minhu's legal guardian?

541
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:21,948
Right now, he is...

542
00:37:26,661 --> 00:37:28,872
(uplifting music)

543
00:37:44,929 --> 00:37:46,556
(pants)

544
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:50,810
(uplifting music continues)

545
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:05,116
I thought you might never
wake up, Mr. Cha.

546
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:07,786
If you didn't wake up today,

547
00:38:08,161 --> 00:38:10,079
I was going to be really mad at you.

548
00:38:12,207 --> 00:38:13,583
Thank God.

549
00:38:13,666 --> 00:38:14,918
Thank you

550
00:38:15,627 --> 00:38:16,961
so much.

551
00:38:23,176 --> 00:38:24,636
Who are you?

552
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:26,721
(music fades)

553
00:38:26,805 --> 00:38:27,806
What?

554
00:38:29,974 --> 00:38:31,184
Do you know me?

555
00:38:32,519 --> 00:38:34,521
(tense music)

556
00:38:34,604 --> 00:38:35,772
What?

557
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:45,657
Stop messing around. It's not funny.

558
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:47,700
Are you trying to get revenge?

559
00:38:47,784 --> 00:38:50,995
You're teasing me
because I didn't remember you, right?

560
00:38:52,622 --> 00:38:53,832
Do you really know me?

561
00:38:54,499 --> 00:38:56,501
I'm Hong Yesool.

562
00:38:56,584 --> 00:39:00,296
We were lovers
who cared deeply about each other.

563
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:04,801
You really, really liked me, so you took
a blade for me, then fell unconscious.

564
00:39:05,426 --> 00:39:07,637
I think that might have
messed with your memories.

565
00:39:08,096 --> 00:39:09,055
I did?

566
00:39:09,848 --> 00:39:15,353
So I saw a future in which we were
sleeping together, so we slept...

567
00:39:15,436 --> 00:39:16,729
You can see the future?

568
00:39:17,146 --> 00:39:18,606
No way. That's impossible.

569
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:21,442
Well, you also had super senses.

570
00:39:21,943 --> 00:39:23,736
No way.

571
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:26,614
We've known each other
since we were little kids.

572
00:39:27,031 --> 00:39:30,326
We always walked around holding hands,
and we painted together at my house.

573
00:39:30,410 --> 00:39:32,996
We took pictures all the time with my dad.

574
00:39:33,496 --> 00:39:35,748
You followed me around all the time...

575
00:39:35,832 --> 00:39:40,295
Hey! You're the one who followed me around
because you liked me so much.

576
00:39:41,045 --> 00:39:42,213
Do you remember now?

577
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:45,592
I was wondering when you would get
your memories back.

578
00:39:46,509 --> 00:39:48,636
-Are you crazy? You're insane!
-(Minhu grunting)

579
00:39:48,720 --> 00:39:50,388
Did you think that was funny?

580
00:39:50,471 --> 00:39:53,516
-Do you know how scared I was?
-I'm injured!

581
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:55,810
I took a blade for you, remember?

582
00:39:55,894 --> 00:39:57,562
Oh, no.

583
00:39:57,645 --> 00:40:00,273
Does it hurt a lot?

584
00:40:03,693 --> 00:40:04,694
(chuckles)

585
00:40:07,363 --> 00:40:09,616
What? What's wrong?

586
00:40:09,699 --> 00:40:11,284
Did you see some awful future again?

587
00:40:11,868 --> 00:40:12,994
No.

588
00:40:13,870 --> 00:40:15,330
I didn't see it.

589
00:40:15,413 --> 00:40:16,539
Didn't see what?

590
00:40:23,421 --> 00:40:25,298
I can't see anything.

591
00:40:25,965 --> 00:40:26,925
Really?

592
00:40:28,468 --> 00:40:30,094
Wait a minute.

593
00:40:30,178 --> 00:40:32,221
My symptoms are gone too.

594
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:41,981
I'm so confused right now.

595
00:40:42,315 --> 00:40:43,775
You can stop now.

596
00:40:43,858 --> 00:40:45,693
I think it's really gone.

597
00:40:47,195 --> 00:40:49,447
Look, I kissed you,
but you're totally fine.

598
00:40:49,989 --> 00:40:51,324
I guess Professor Oh was right.

599
00:40:51,699 --> 00:40:53,534
Professor Oh? Did you meet him?

600
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:55,495
What did he say?

601
00:40:56,412 --> 00:40:59,290
He said we got our abilities
so we could protect each other.

602
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:01,250
Wait, so,

603
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:03,211
it just disappeared after that?

604
00:41:03,294 --> 00:41:04,837
Don't you think it's a good thing?

605
00:41:04,921 --> 00:41:07,548
You said you wanted to live a normal life.

606
00:41:07,632 --> 00:41:10,969
Now you can have a normal love life too.

607
00:41:11,636 --> 00:41:15,264
I mean, how can it just
disappear so suddenly...

608
00:41:15,765 --> 00:41:17,934
I guess you don't need it anymore.

609
00:41:19,936 --> 00:41:24,399
More importantly...

610
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:27,402
My gosh, who are you?
Why are you taking off my clothes?

611
00:41:27,819 --> 00:41:29,696
Do you know me? I don't know you.

612
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:31,864
Hey, thanks to that,
you didn't start crying.

613
00:41:31,948 --> 00:41:33,616
Do you know how much it hurt me

614
00:41:33,700 --> 00:41:37,120
to listen to you cry yourself to sleep
every day when I was unconscious?

615
00:41:37,954 --> 00:41:40,373
You heard all that?

616
00:41:40,748 --> 00:41:42,458
I'm saying that you probably did that.

617
00:41:42,542 --> 00:41:43,918
Because you like me so much.

618
00:41:44,002 --> 00:41:46,129
So you must have cried a lot.

619
00:41:46,462 --> 00:41:47,755
Whatever.

620
00:41:47,839 --> 00:41:50,466
And I bet you prayed
every night too, like this.

621
00:41:50,550 --> 00:41:54,303
"Please, God, if he wakes up,
I'll do anything!"

622
00:41:56,806 --> 00:41:57,807
Oh!

623
00:41:58,266 --> 00:41:59,434
It doesn't hurt?

624
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:00,893
It hurts.

625
00:42:00,977 --> 00:42:02,311
Are you crazy?

626
00:42:02,395 --> 00:42:03,604
(both grunt)

627
00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:05,898
Don't be a baby.

628
00:42:06,399 --> 00:42:08,026
Are you a pervert or something?

629
00:42:08,109 --> 00:42:09,736
Why would you unbutton my shirt like that?

630
00:42:10,403 --> 00:42:12,488
I need to keep it shut tight.

631
00:42:13,072 --> 00:42:14,157
Come on, Yesool.

632
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:17,118
-Hey!
-Yesool.

633
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:19,704
Yesool.

634
00:42:19,787 --> 00:42:21,914
-Come on!
-(Yesool yells)

635
00:42:21,998 --> 00:42:22,623
Take off your socks.

636
00:42:24,625 --> 00:42:26,419
Is that where the logo is supposed to be?

637
00:42:26,502 --> 00:42:28,629
Isn't it supposed to be
on the right, not the left?

638
00:42:28,713 --> 00:42:31,424
In the first draft, it was morning,

639
00:42:31,883 --> 00:42:33,051
but now the sun's setting.

640
00:42:34,385 --> 00:42:36,804
Still, it's not bad.

641
00:42:37,513 --> 00:42:38,681
Yes.

642
00:42:39,432 --> 00:42:41,059
(sighs)
I guess Planning Team 1

643
00:42:41,476 --> 00:42:43,686
doesn't really need us anymore.

644
00:42:46,064 --> 00:42:48,149
Well, they have a great team leader.

645
00:42:48,524 --> 00:42:50,109
I'm the one who made them so good.

646
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:57,325
Mr. Cha, you remember everything
about my father, right?

647
00:42:57,992 --> 00:42:58,993
Yes.

648
00:42:59,577 --> 00:43:02,455
He's the reason I started working at Zeu.

649
00:43:03,164 --> 00:43:06,292
Wow, and you didn't tell me?

650
00:43:06,375 --> 00:43:08,419
What a weirdo.

651
00:43:08,503 --> 00:43:11,422
Hey. Do you know how hard
it's been for me?

652
00:43:11,506 --> 00:43:13,674
I was always wondering
when you would remember me,

653
00:43:13,758 --> 00:43:15,968
and I wanted to tell you
everything so many times.

654
00:43:16,052 --> 00:43:19,013
But I found out
why you didn't remember me,

655
00:43:19,097 --> 00:43:20,306
so I couldn't tell you.

656
00:43:20,389 --> 00:43:23,059
You still should've told me.

657
00:43:23,935 --> 00:43:27,980
Don't you know why I couldn't tell you,
even though I really wanted to?

658
00:43:29,899 --> 00:43:31,025
That.

659
00:43:32,652 --> 00:43:33,778
I couldn't believe it.

660
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:38,699
I found you again just to see you
dating another guy.

661
00:43:39,200 --> 00:43:41,494
On top of that, you really didn't
want to break up with him.

662
00:43:41,577 --> 00:43:42,787
I was trying to be nice...

663
00:43:44,288 --> 00:43:45,498
Whatever.

664
00:43:46,082 --> 00:43:47,291
Just look at this.

665
00:43:47,375 --> 00:43:50,586
You brought your boyfriend to a place
that was special for you and your ex.

666
00:43:50,670 --> 00:43:51,712
What's this?

667
00:43:55,133 --> 00:43:56,259
"Hong Yesool"?

668
00:44:04,892 --> 00:44:07,311
PILYO: Hong Yesool,
I'm leaving you this letter

669
00:44:07,395 --> 00:44:09,730
because I think you'll visit this place
at least once

670
00:44:10,314 --> 00:44:11,816
before it's taken down.

671
00:44:13,192 --> 00:44:16,946
Even when I was far away from you,
I always wondered

672
00:44:17,738 --> 00:44:18,948
if you were doing well,

673
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:20,950
if you had stopped crying,

674
00:44:21,617 --> 00:44:23,828
if you were living a good life,

675
00:44:24,203 --> 00:44:25,621
and if you were loving someone

676
00:44:26,164 --> 00:44:27,373
and being loved.

677
00:44:28,166 --> 00:44:29,625
So, I'm thankful

678
00:44:30,334 --> 00:44:33,796
that I got to see you smile before I left.

679
00:44:34,422 --> 00:44:37,717
People say you need to throw away
everything from a relationship

680
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:39,010
after you break up,

681
00:44:39,552 --> 00:44:40,845
but I disagree.

682
00:44:41,846 --> 00:44:45,016
I can't throw away the years
and memories that I shared with you,

683
00:44:45,099 --> 00:44:47,768
and the words we said to each other,

684
00:44:48,269 --> 00:44:49,812
and the feelings that we shared.

685
00:44:50,396 --> 00:44:51,856
I'm going to hold on to

686
00:44:52,398 --> 00:44:53,691
the love

687
00:44:54,192 --> 00:44:55,693
that we shared

688
00:44:56,444 --> 00:44:58,613
in the past.

689
00:44:59,155 --> 00:45:02,658
The me of the past will always remember

690
00:45:03,784 --> 00:45:05,745
the you of the past.

691
00:45:07,455 --> 00:45:08,956
So, Hong Yesool,

692
00:45:09,999 --> 00:45:11,417
be happy.

693
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:16,672
PS You didn't keep the promise
that you would meet with me three times,

694
00:45:17,423 --> 00:45:20,593
but I'll forgive you,
since I'm so understanding and a genius.

695
00:45:24,597 --> 00:45:25,848
MINHU: Don't cry.

696
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:30,102
If you cry right now,
I'm going to be furious.

697
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:32,563
I mean, look,

698
00:45:32,647 --> 00:45:34,982
he's just so good at writing.

699
00:45:35,066 --> 00:45:36,567
Here, read it.

700
00:45:36,651 --> 00:45:38,694
Why would I read it? What a weirdo.

701
00:45:39,195 --> 00:45:40,279
You're insane!

702
00:45:40,738 --> 00:45:42,782
Hey, wait for me!

703
00:45:48,704 --> 00:45:49,789
I love you.

704
00:45:51,999 --> 00:45:56,462
I really, really like you,
and I missed you so much.

705
00:45:58,047 --> 00:45:59,382
I'm glad that I got stabbed.

706
00:46:02,551 --> 00:46:06,305
I'm going to stay right next to you
and just love you forever.

707
00:46:08,432 --> 00:46:12,687
YESOOL: You might not believe me,
but I had a superpower.

708
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:18,317
I could see somebody's future
if my lips touched their body.

709
00:46:19,944 --> 00:46:23,990
Let's always stay together, okay?

710
00:46:26,284 --> 00:46:27,827
Do you want to get married, then?

711
00:46:27,910 --> 00:46:29,996
-No.
-What?

712
00:46:30,454 --> 00:46:32,832
Didn't you just say
that you want to stay together forever?

713
00:46:32,915 --> 00:46:36,752
I meant, let's never break up,

714
00:46:37,211 --> 00:46:39,213
date for just a bit longer,

715
00:46:39,297 --> 00:46:41,257
and do whatever we want to do.

716
00:46:41,340 --> 00:46:42,300
Like what?

717
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:43,926
Like...

718
00:46:47,388 --> 00:46:48,306
This.

719
00:46:49,181 --> 00:46:51,350
YESOOL: I got this ability 23 years ago.

720
00:46:52,226 --> 00:46:56,605
It's an ability that disappeared
as soon as I figured out why I got it.

721
00:46:57,773 --> 00:47:01,610
Now, I can't see the future anymore,
but one thing is for sure.

722
00:47:02,403 --> 00:47:04,780
He'll be with me.

723
00:47:05,656 --> 00:47:09,702
He'll be my lover forever.

724
00:47:09,785 --> 00:47:11,370
-MINHU: Don't let go.
-YESOOL: Okay!

725
00:47:11,454 --> 00:47:13,205
We're meant to be...

726
00:47:13,289 --> 00:47:14,457
My a**.

727
00:47:15,666 --> 00:47:16,959
Let's break up.

728
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:20,338
-Are you being serious?
-Yes.

729
00:47:20,421 --> 00:47:23,007
I can't date someone like you anymore.

730
00:47:24,133 --> 00:47:25,468
What did you just say?

731
00:47:26,093 --> 00:47:28,012
How is it my fault
that you lost your phone?

732
00:47:28,095 --> 00:47:29,972
-YESOOL: If we're really meant to be...
-I looked for it

733
00:47:30,056 --> 00:47:31,932
-for three hours...
-...we wouldn't fight like this

734
00:47:32,016 --> 00:47:33,684
-every day.
-...and now you want to break up?

735
00:47:33,768 --> 00:47:36,103
YESOOL: Well, you never found it.

736
00:47:36,187 --> 00:47:38,272
All of my work contacts
and notes are on that phone.

737
00:47:38,731 --> 00:47:41,233
I wish you still had your superpowers.

738
00:47:41,317 --> 00:47:43,694
You looked for three hours,
and you couldn't find a phone?

739
00:47:43,778 --> 00:47:45,780
How on earth am I supposed
to find your phone?

740
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:48,532
Do you think I'm a dog? Woof, woof, woof!

741
00:47:48,616 --> 00:47:54,038
You used to be so put together,
and now you're just crazy.

742
00:47:54,121 --> 00:47:57,375
Then why don't you just see the future
so you don't lose your darn phone?

743
00:47:57,792 --> 00:47:59,001
Just say it.

744
00:47:59,085 --> 00:48:01,629
I know you're not really mad at me
because of the phone.

745
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:04,423
No. You're acting like this
because I talked with Ms. Yoon

746
00:48:04,507 --> 00:48:05,549
from our client company!

747
00:48:05,633 --> 00:48:10,096
Oh, so you just "talked" with her
while smiling at her the entire time?

748
00:48:10,596 --> 00:48:13,516
You even secretly texted her last night.

749
00:48:13,933 --> 00:48:16,519
That was for work.

750
00:48:16,602 --> 00:48:18,938
Then why did you do it
at eight in the evening?

751
00:48:19,063 --> 00:48:22,691
And why was Ms. Yoon
sending those damn smiley faces

752
00:48:22,775 --> 00:48:24,568
with her texts?

753
00:48:25,569 --> 00:48:29,073
I can't believe you said
that we're meant to be.

754
00:48:29,156 --> 00:48:31,659
You're always picking a fight
over the dumbest things.

755
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:33,953
Hey, I'm sick of it too.

756
00:48:34,036 --> 00:48:36,163
I've never had such a terrible boyfriend!

757
00:48:36,247 --> 00:48:37,289
What?

758
00:48:37,665 --> 00:48:40,126
I hope you're not going to regret
what you just said.

759
00:48:40,501 --> 00:48:42,253
Why would I regret it?

760
00:48:42,336 --> 00:48:43,712
-Geez.
-Damn it.

761
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:46,340
(quirky music)

762
00:48:51,011 --> 00:48:52,555
I'm sorry.

763
00:48:52,638 --> 00:48:53,848
I'll block Ms. Yoon's number.

764
00:48:57,852 --> 00:48:59,270
I'm sorry too.

765
00:48:59,770 --> 00:49:01,689
Maybe I should get some therapy.

766
00:49:01,939 --> 00:49:04,650
I'm sorry. It was my fault. Let's go home.

767
00:49:05,359 --> 00:49:06,694
-Block her.
-Okay.

768
00:49:06,777 --> 00:49:10,698
YESOOL: That's how
our normal relationship started.

769
00:49:10,781 --> 00:49:12,992
(crowd laugh)

770
00:49:18,873 --> 00:49:20,124
I'm going to the bathroom.

771
00:49:21,417 --> 00:49:23,586
(upbeat music)

772
00:49:33,471 --> 00:49:34,972
Do you like the movie?

773
00:49:35,890 --> 00:49:37,016
Who are you?

774
00:49:37,808 --> 00:49:38,976
Hey!

775
00:49:39,894 --> 00:49:41,270
I'm sorry.

776
00:49:42,688 --> 00:49:47,860
YESOOL: Without our abilities,
we turned out to be a lot less dependable.

777
00:49:47,943 --> 00:49:49,195
(scoffs)

778
00:49:52,072 --> 00:49:54,408
You told me to trust you.

779
00:49:55,326 --> 00:49:58,370
How was I supposed to know
that our flight would get canceled?

780
00:49:58,454 --> 00:50:00,873
I told you we should
go on vacation next week.

781
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:04,126
So the weather forecast was wrong.
Why are you taking it out on me?

782
00:50:04,627 --> 00:50:06,879
You were so sure
when you booked our flights,

783
00:50:06,962 --> 00:50:09,173
that I thought you saw
the future or something!

784
00:50:09,965 --> 00:50:11,884
(thunder rumbles)

785
00:50:11,967 --> 00:50:13,302
I'm going home!

786
00:50:14,720 --> 00:50:16,764
-Hey!
-YESOOL: I couldn't see the future...

787
00:50:16,847 --> 00:50:17,723
Hey.

788
00:50:17,806 --> 00:50:20,017
...and I had no idea what would
happen in the next minute.

789
00:50:20,518 --> 00:50:23,521
Dating Cha Minhu is so hard.

790
00:50:23,604 --> 00:50:28,567
Whenever I meet with him, I'm so tired
that I can't even take a shower or eat.

791
00:50:29,068 --> 00:50:32,947
It's annoying, right?
So let's just live together.

792
00:50:33,948 --> 00:50:38,702
Dating you like this is hard for me too.

793
00:50:38,786 --> 00:50:40,120
So let's live together.

794
00:50:42,831 --> 00:50:44,124
Wow.

795
00:50:44,208 --> 00:50:46,085
I don't even know where to start.

796
00:50:46,168 --> 00:50:48,546
Maybe at "It's annoying."

797
00:50:48,879 --> 00:50:51,924
Or maybe "Dating you like this is hard
for me too, so let's live together"?

798
00:50:53,050 --> 00:50:56,470
"Annoying" and "let's live together."
Why are those two together?

799
00:50:56,554 --> 00:50:58,847
Do you date me just so
you can argue with me?

800
00:50:58,931 --> 00:51:00,307
Then let's just break up!

801
00:51:00,391 --> 00:51:02,101
Hey! I've told you before.

802
00:51:02,184 --> 00:51:03,686
If you say that again, then I--

803
00:51:03,769 --> 00:51:04,979
Let's really break up!

804
00:51:06,480 --> 00:51:08,315
It was just one of our many fights,

805
00:51:08,899 --> 00:51:10,025
but we ended up...

806
