01:04:16,352 --> 01:04:17,479
(scoffs)

1064
01:04:19,731 --> 01:04:22,025
(soft chuckle)
Did I surprise you?

1065
01:04:22,650 --> 01:04:24,736
I mean, the movie character.

1066
01:04:24,819 --> 01:04:27,739
Well, I do like that name too.

1067
01:04:27,822 --> 01:04:31,701
I found out that in the movie,
I'll get to kiss Cha Minhu,

1068
01:04:31,785 --> 01:04:35,663
and you know, do other things too.

1069
01:04:35,747 --> 01:04:37,665
Oh, my God, what is she even saying?

1070
01:04:37,749 --> 01:04:40,210
-HOST: The character, Cha Minhu...
-Does she have some kind of complex?

1071
01:04:40,293 --> 01:04:42,003
I think she might have a mental illness.

1072
01:04:42,087 --> 01:04:45,507
Honestly, I think she likes me
more than Cha Minhu.

1073
01:04:45,590 --> 01:04:47,050
She's just trying to piss me off.

1074
01:04:47,133 --> 01:04:49,803
-HOST: Produced by JTBS,
-Is that jealousy I hear?

1075
01:04:49,886 --> 01:04:52,889
-HOST: it won award after award overseas.
-No way.

1076
01:04:52,972 --> 01:04:56,309
To be jealous,
you need to like that person first.

1077
01:04:56,392 --> 01:04:58,394
Why would I be jealous?
We've already broken up.

1078
01:04:58,478 --> 01:05:00,355
-Whatever.
-Let me ask you the next question.

1079
01:05:00,438 --> 01:05:01,815
Hey, this is mine too.

1080
01:05:02,565 --> 01:05:05,568
Wow, you're really good at
finding those, aren't you?

1081
01:05:05,652 --> 01:05:08,071
Hey, don't forget this.

1082
01:05:08,154 --> 01:05:10,156
HOST:
The fans were very excited when they heard

1083
01:05:10,657 --> 01:05:12,992
that you two
were going to be working together.

1084
01:05:13,076 --> 01:05:17,705
I would like to know a bit more
about your first meeting.

1085
01:05:17,789 --> 01:05:21,459
What were your first impressions
of each other?

1086
01:05:23,586 --> 01:05:24,754
Mr. Lee.

1087
01:05:26,548 --> 01:05:28,049
How do you feel about me?

1088
01:05:29,592 --> 01:05:30,635
Do you like me?

1089
01:05:31,261 --> 01:05:32,929
(quirky music)

1090
01:05:33,763 --> 01:05:35,390
(camera shutter clicks)

1091
01:05:35,473 --> 01:05:36,474
(scoffs)

1092
01:05:37,058 --> 01:05:38,434
As an actress.

1093
01:05:40,061 --> 01:05:41,271
(sighs)

1094
01:05:41,896 --> 01:05:43,898
Of course, I do.

1095
01:05:44,357 --> 01:05:46,067
Ms. Oh, you're so professional and--

1096
01:05:46,151 --> 01:05:47,777
How about as a woman?

1097
01:05:47,861 --> 01:05:49,863
(playful music)

1098
01:05:50,780 --> 01:05:51,990
(scoffs)

1099
01:05:52,073 --> 01:05:53,533
(camera shutter clicks)

1100
01:05:54,075 --> 01:05:56,870
Ms. Oh, why would you say that
at an event like this?

1101
01:05:56,953 --> 01:05:59,205
I'm asking you
because we're at this event.

1102
01:05:59,289 --> 01:06:02,083
I wanted to ask you this question
in front of a lot of people.

1103
01:06:03,626 --> 01:06:05,086
If I asked you an actual question,

1104
01:06:05,587 --> 01:06:07,964
you said you'd give me
an actual response, right?

1105
01:06:08,464 --> 01:06:09,591
What do you think of me?

1106
01:06:15,513 --> 01:06:16,723
Then what about you?

1107
01:06:19,851 --> 01:06:21,769
-I like you.
-(audience gasping)

1108
01:06:21,853 --> 01:06:25,982
I like all of your movies and works.

1109
01:06:26,566 --> 01:06:30,153
And I think the person
who made those movies is a good person.

1110
01:06:30,862 --> 01:06:36,367
The person I've been spending time with
is a good person too.

1111
01:06:37,744 --> 01:06:39,954
I don't know
when I started feeling this way,

1112
01:06:40,538 --> 01:06:41,539
but I...

1113
01:06:43,208 --> 01:06:44,125
like you.

1114
01:06:44,751 --> 01:06:46,920
(audience clamoring)

1115
01:06:51,925 --> 01:06:53,176
No way.

1116
01:06:53,259 --> 01:06:54,302
No way.

1117
01:06:54,385 --> 01:06:56,387
(audience cheer)

1118
01:06:59,432 --> 01:07:02,560
HOST: I'm sure the entire country just saw
Ms. Oh confessing her feelings.

1119
01:07:02,644 --> 01:07:04,020
Wasn't that romantic?

1120
01:07:04,479 --> 01:07:07,982
That was like a scene from a movie,
wasn't it?

1121
01:07:12,237 --> 01:07:13,446
Everyone,

1122
01:07:13,529 --> 01:07:17,742
please make sure to give the movie, Her,
your love and attention.

1123
01:07:21,704 --> 01:07:23,289
Wow, that's annoying.

1124
01:07:23,623 --> 01:07:25,333
Wait, what do you mean?

1125
01:07:26,334 --> 01:07:30,421
The person who said that
he'd love me to the moon and back

1126
01:07:30,505 --> 01:07:33,132
just fights with me all the time.

1127
01:07:33,841 --> 01:07:34,926
(grunts)

1128
01:07:38,304 --> 01:07:39,806
I'm going to take this too.

1129
01:07:39,889 --> 01:07:40,974
(yells)

1130
01:07:41,057 --> 01:07:42,267
Hey, that's mine.

1131
01:07:42,809 --> 01:07:44,852
It's mine! I helped paint it.

1132
01:07:44,936 --> 01:07:46,562
Look, my name's on it!

1133
01:07:46,938 --> 01:07:48,773
It's not like you remembered it!

1134
01:07:49,315 --> 01:07:51,317
Now I wish
I had never gotten my memories back.

1135
01:07:51,401 --> 01:07:52,860
The Minhu I used to know is gone.

1136
01:07:53,403 --> 01:07:54,654
Well, this is who I am.

1137
01:07:57,740 --> 01:07:59,617
This is your last chance.

1138
01:07:59,701 --> 01:08:02,537
If you leave right now,
this is really the end.

1139
01:08:02,620 --> 01:08:04,372
Is there a fake "the end"?

1140
01:08:04,455 --> 01:08:06,082
I could tell you the same thing.

1141
01:08:06,165 --> 01:08:07,875
Don't you dare drunk dial me again.

1142
01:08:07,959 --> 01:08:10,962
You've called me
way more times than I did.

1143
01:08:11,045 --> 01:08:13,047
If you call me again,
I'm going to get a new number!

1144
01:08:13,131 --> 01:08:14,882
And don't get drunk and knock on my door!

1145
01:08:14,966 --> 01:08:16,342
I could tell you the same thing!

1146
01:08:16,426 --> 01:08:18,511
The security guard at my building
pretends to be asleep

1147
01:08:18,594 --> 01:08:19,971
whenever he sees you coming!

1148
01:08:21,347 --> 01:08:23,474
-Whatever.
-Take it!

1149
01:08:23,558 --> 01:08:24,809
YESOOL: Just throw it in the dumpster!

1150
01:08:25,184 --> 01:08:26,394
(door slams)

1151
01:08:27,353 --> 01:08:28,813
(exhales deeply)

1152
01:08:32,817 --> 01:08:35,236
(light music)

1153
01:08:50,710 --> 01:08:53,755
I'm walking so slowly,
but he's not even going to follow me?

1154
01:08:57,050 --> 01:08:58,885
He said I was his only love.

1155
01:09:00,136 --> 01:09:01,888
MINHU: You really are my only love.

1156
01:09:02,555 --> 01:09:03,681
(sighs)

1157
01:09:05,641 --> 01:09:07,643
(pants)

1158
01:09:11,439 --> 01:09:13,232
Before, you would've already
caught up to me.

1159
01:09:13,316 --> 01:09:16,527
No, you wouldn't have let me
leave like this in the first place.

1160
01:09:16,611 --> 01:09:18,905
I didn't know you would walk this way.

1161
01:09:19,322 --> 01:09:21,908
I ran here from the bus stop
that you usually go to.

1162
01:09:22,450 --> 01:09:23,743
I'm so tired.

1163
01:09:24,410 --> 01:09:25,787
You didn't even get that right.

1164
01:09:25,870 --> 01:09:28,206
Before, I never had to tell you
where I was going.

1165
01:09:28,289 --> 01:09:30,166
Well, I'm not the person
that I used to be.

1166
01:09:30,958 --> 01:09:34,045
But, look. I still found you.

1167
01:09:34,962 --> 01:09:37,924
Even if you want to leave me,
I'll hold on to you.

1168
01:09:39,217 --> 01:09:40,802
And I'll find you faster next time.

1169
01:09:41,469 --> 01:09:44,722
So, let's call a truce for today.

1170
01:09:47,350 --> 01:09:48,393
Fine. Truce.

1171
01:09:49,060 --> 01:09:51,521
Don't start talking about
destiny or whatever.

1172
01:09:51,604 --> 01:09:52,897
Just focus on loving me today.

1173
01:09:52,980 --> 01:09:55,400
You too. Don't tell me
that you'll love me forever

1174
01:09:55,483 --> 01:09:56,651
until you die or something.

1175
01:09:56,734 --> 01:09:58,361
Love me right here, right now.

1176
01:09:59,278 --> 01:10:00,446
(smirks)

1177
01:10:04,158 --> 01:10:05,368
(sighs deeply)

1178
01:10:06,160 --> 01:10:10,331
YESOOL: We might not be
destined for each other.

1179
01:10:11,207 --> 01:10:14,711
We'll just have to keep fighting
and apologizing like this.

1180
01:10:14,794 --> 01:10:18,881
Destiny? We'll just write it ourselves
as we go.

1181
01:10:26,055 --> 01:10:27,432
I want to kiss you.

1182
01:10:29,517 --> 01:10:30,518
Right here?

1183
01:10:30,601 --> 01:10:31,769
Yes.

1184
01:10:32,270 --> 01:10:34,522
(upbeat music)

1185
01:10:43,614 --> 01:10:49,787
YESOOL: That's our love story,
without any superpowers.

1186
01:10:51,205 --> 01:10:53,207
(dramatic music)

1187
01:10:59,338 --> 01:11:01,174
(gasps)
No!

1188
01:11:04,802 --> 01:11:06,804
(theme music)

1189
01:11:58,105 --> 01:12:00,107
(closing theme music)
